value.def: Your elbow is the part of your arm where the upper and lower halves of the arm are joined.

example.ex: He slipped and fell, badly bruising an elbow.
example.tran: 他滑倒了，一只胳膊肘严重擦伤。

value.def: If you elbow people aside or elbow your way somewhere, you push people with your elbows in order to move somewhere.

example.ex: They also claim that the security team elbowed aside a steward...
example.tran: 他们还声称保安人员将一位乘务员推搡至一边。

example.ex: Mr Smith elbowed me in the face...
example.tran: 史密斯先生一肘撞在我脸上。

example.ex: Brand elbowed his way to the centre of the group of bystanders.
example.tran: 布兰德挤到看热闹的人群中央。

value.def: If someone or something elbows their way somewhere, or elbows other people or things out of the way, they achieve success by being aggressive and determined.

example.ex: Non-state firms gradually elbow aside the inefficient state-owned ones...
example.tran: 非国有企业逐渐挤掉了效率低下的国有企业。

example.ex: Environmental concerns will elbow their way right to the top of the agenda.
example.tran: 环境问题将挤到议事日程之首。
